==English==

===Etymology===
Dutch : "niks".(nothing) Although it's slang for "niets" (nothing), it is in the Dutch dictionary and is used by virtually all classes of society.
 
Maybe also from German: "nichts", pronounced [nɪçtz], colloquial "nix" [nɪkz], meaning "nothing"

===Noun===
{{en-noun-unc}}

# {{colloquial}}: [[nothing]].

===Etymology===
Named after the mother of [[Charon]], godess of [[darkness]] and [[light]].
# Nix: The name of one of the moons of [[Pluto]] (named 23 June 2006)

